{"TopicId":176273,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Is there a mod for terrain levelling?","CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-29T14:57:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-29T14:57:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have two\u00A0contracts\u00A0I\u0027d like to combine them into one, one for a Mun base and the other for mining ore. \u00A0The best equatorial ore location looks to be\u00A0in a canyon with very little level terrain.\u00A0Rather than convoy ore in and out of the canyon I\u0027d like to level out spots for a landing pad and the base itself.\u00A0Is there a mod to simulate grading a surface to be a level?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-29T15:32:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbal Konstructs *might* be able to level a section of the Mun for you, but it doesn\u0027t really simulate grading a surface.\u00A0 In general, that\u0027s hard as KSP treats \u0027terrain\u0027 as different than \u0027ships\u0027, and terrain is pretty much un-alterable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are a few other solutions.\u00A0 Though note that your drills will need to actually hit the terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIdeas:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStockalike Station Parts Redux has some nifty self-leveling legs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8296896542\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/170211-142-stockalike-station-parts-redux-april-10/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtraplanetary Launchpads or Ground Construction can be used to build a base with launch clamps - which will hold you level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3181753950\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/54284-144-extraplanetary-launchpads-v610/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1338835030\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154167-143-ground-construction-2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E can be used to anchor parts to the ground:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3084936129\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149848-14-kerbal-inventory-system-kis-v112/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, I believe Pathfinder is working on being able to build platforms (and I\u0027ve seen \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106975\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Angel-125\u003C/a\u003E demo it), though I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s ready yet:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5286732395\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/121397-14x-pathfinder-space-camping-geoscience/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-29T19:12:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, for the suggestions,\u00A0I\u0027ve been using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E for a while and was aware of most of the others. Taking off and base construction are less of a concern for me than the idea of\u00A0making a level landing pad to make landing easier. I\u0027m already using:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2968518977\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/133606-13114x-kerbal-planetary-base-systems-v164-1-june-2018/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:227px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-03T11:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe there was a high explosives mod that was able to maes in the landscale, effectivly allowing you to make channels in the landscape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}